Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSER STATE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The parser holds the lexer, the source pointer (for lexeme extraction), and the
single lookahead token decomposed into its kind/start/end fields. A
last_progress field tracks the lexer byte cursor seen at the start of each
list/block loop iteration so any loop can detect zero progress and force an
advance, structurally preventing the non-advancing-loop class of bug.
@End Reasoning
Type called "KotlinParser":
    lexer as Integer
    source as Integer
    cur_type as Integer
    cur_start as Integer
    cur_end as Integer
    had_error as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Builds a parser bound to a lexer and primes the lookahead with the first token.
Field layout (48 bytes): lexer@0, source@8, cur_type@16, cur_start@24,
cur_end@32, had_error@40.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_parser" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with 56
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, source
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 48, 0
    proc advance with parser
    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
in_when_body (offset 48) is a depth counter set while parsing a when-arm body's
top-level expression. Because the lexer discards newlines (Kotlin's actual
when-arm separator), parse_named_infix must not absorb a leading is/!is/in/infix
identifier that in fact begins the NEXT when arm. This flag suppresses that
continuation exactly at the when-arm body boundary while leaving full infix
support everywhere else.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_in_when_body" takes parser as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 48, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "get_in_when_body" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 48
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST NODE HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates a 64-byte AST node. Layout (shared with kotlin_semantic and
kotlin_to_hir): node_type@0, children(List)@8, name@16, value@24,
modifiers(List)@32, type_ref@40, aux1@48, aux2@56. The children list is
created eagerly so consumers can iterate it with the List primitive without a
null guard.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 56, 0
    Return node
End Process

Process called "node_add_child" takes node as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
    proc add from List with children, child
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "node_set_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, name
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "node_set_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "node_set_type_ref" takes node as Integer, type_ref as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, type_ref
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "node_set_aux1" takes node as Integer, aux as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, aux
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "node_set_aux2" takes node as Integer, aux as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 56, aux
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lazily allocates the node's modifiers list (offset 32) and appends a modifier
string. Modifiers are stored as raw string pointers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_add_modifier" takes node as Integer, modifier as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mods be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32
    If mods is equal to 0:
        Set mods to proc create from List
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, mods
    End If
    proc add from List with mods, modifier
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOKEN STREAM
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Pulls the next token from the lexer and decomposes it into the parser's
lookahead fields. Always replaces the lookahead, so a call to advance is a
guaranteed forward step in the token stream whenever the lexer is not at EOF.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let token be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
    Let ttype be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0
    Let tstart be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 8
    Let tend be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, ttype
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, tstart
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, tend
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "cur" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
End Process

Process called "at_eof" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the lexeme of the current token as an owned NUL-terminated string,
copied out of the source between the token's start and end. Copying (rather
than aliasing) is required because subsequent advances reuse the lexer buffer
position; the AST must own its name/value strings.
@End Reasoning
Process called "cur_text" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Let start be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 24
    Let end_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 32
    Return proc kotlin_substring with source, start, end_pos
End Process

Process called "kotlin_substring" takes source as Integer, start_pos as Integer, end_pos as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be end_pos minus start_pos
    If len is less than 0:
        Set len to 0
    End If
    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with len plus 1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, start_pos plus i
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, i, ch
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, len, 0
    Return buffer
End Process

Process called "check" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    If t is equal to token_type:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
If the current token matches, consume it (advance) and return 1; otherwise
return 0 without consuming. Used to optionally accept punctuation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "accept" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    If t is equal to token_type:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consumes the current token if it matches the expected kind; on mismatch sets
the parser error flag but still advances one token so the caller's loop makes
progress (error recovery). This guarantees expect can never cause a stall.
@End Reasoning
Process called "expect" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    If t is equal to token_type:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, 1
    If t is not equal to TOKEN_EOF:
        proc advance with parser
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reads the lexer's byte cursor (position@8). Used by every list/block loop to
detect zero forward progress between successive iterations and force a recovery
advance, eliminating the non-advancing-loop bug class.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lexer_cursor" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
End Process

Process called "force_advance" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc advance with parser
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOP LEVEL
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a complete Kotlin file: an optional package header, a run of imports,
then top-level declarations until EOF. The declaration loop reads the lexer
cursor before and after each sub-parse and force-advances on zero progress, so
an unparseable token can never stall the loop.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_compilation_unit" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let program be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PROGRAM

    Note: package header
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_PACKAGE is equal to 1:
        Let pkg be proc parse_package with parser
        proc node_add_child with program, pkg
    End If

    Note: imports
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_IMPORT is equal to 1:
        Let imp be proc parse_import with parser
        proc node_add_child with program, imp
    End While

    Note: top-level declarations
    While proc at_eof with parser is equal to 0:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let decl be proc parse_declaration with parser
        If decl is not equal to 0:
            proc node_add_child with program, decl
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While

    Return program
End Process

Process called "parse_package" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_PACKAGE
    Let name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PACKAGE
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses an import path which may end with `.*` (wildcard) and optionally an `as`
alias. The alias and wildcard flag are stored in value/aux fields so the
backend can reproduce the exact import form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_import" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IMPORT
    Let name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IMPORT

    Note: wildcard import: trailing .* . parse_qualified_name already consumed the
    Note: final '.' and left the cursor on the '*', so check for STAR directly.
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_STAR is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Set name to proc str3 with name, ".", "*"
    Otherwise:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_DOT is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_STAR is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
                Set name to proc str3 with name, ".", "*"
            End If
        End If
    End If
    proc node_set_name with node, name

    Note: import alias
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_AS is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let alias be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_value with node, alias
    End If

    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reads a dotted identifier path (A.B.C). Each segment is any identifier-or-
soft-keyword token; segments are joined with '.'. The loop force-advances on
zero progress (it always consumes at least the leading identifier).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_qualified_name" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_DOT is equal to 1:
        Let save be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Note: stop on .* wildcard (handled by caller)
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_STAR is equal to 1:
            Note: put back conceptually: append nothing, leave star for caller
            Set name to name
            Return name
        End If
        Let seg be proc cur_text with parser
        Set name to proc str3 with name, ".", seg
        proc advance with parser
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to save:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    Return name
End Process

Process called "str3" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ab be proc string_concat_local with a, b
    Return proc string_concat_local with ab, c
End Process

@Reasoning:
Length-summing concatenation of two NUL-terminated strings into a fresh buffer.
Kept local so the parser has no dependency beyond StringCore/Layout.
@End Reasoning
Process called "string_concat_local" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let la be proc string_length from StringCore with a
    Let lb be proc string_length from StringCore with b
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with la plus lb plus 1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than la:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with a, i
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buf, i, ch
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than lb:
        Let ch2 be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with b, j
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buf, la plus j, ch2
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buf, la plus lb, 0
    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MODIFIERS AND ANNOTATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Collects a run of leading annotations (@Name(args?)) and modifier keywords into
a list, returning it. This is shared by every declaration form. The loop reads
the cursor each iteration and force-advances on zero progress.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_modifiers" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mods be proc create from List
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let t be proc cur with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_ANNOTATION_USE:
            proc advance with parser
            Let aname be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            Note: optional annotation argument list - skip balanced parens
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
                proc skip_balanced_parens with parser
            End If
            Let amod be proc str3 with "@", aname, ""
            proc add from List with mods, amod
        Otherwise:
            If proc is_modifier_token with t is equal to 1:
                Let mtext be proc cur_text with parser
                proc advance with parser
                proc add from List with mods, mtext
            Otherwise:
                Set looping to 0
            End If
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            If looping is equal to 1:
                proc force_advance with parser
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return mods
End Process

Process called "is_modifier_token" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INTERNAL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_OPEN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_ABSTRACT:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_OVERRIDE:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SEALED:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DATA:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INNER:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INLINE:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SUSPEND:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_OPERATOR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INFIX:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_LATEINIT:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CONST:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_VARARG:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_REIFIED:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: 'annotation' stays a modifier so `annotation class X` is recognised by
    Note: parse_class via mods_contains "annotation".
    If t is equal to TOKEN_ANNOTATION:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: 'companion' is NOT treated as a general modifier: it must route to
    Note: parse_companion through the declaration dispatcher, otherwise the
    Note: following `object` body would be misparsed.
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "copy_modifiers_to_node" takes node as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    If mods is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with mods
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let m be proc get from List with mods, i
        proc node_add_modifier with node, m
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Skips a balanced parenthesised region (used for annotation argument lists we do
not need to model structurally). Tracks paren depth and force-advances on every
iteration via the token stream, so it always terminates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "skip_balanced_parens" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc advance with parser
    Let depth be 1
    While depth is greater than 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN:
            Set depth to depth plus 1
        End If
        If t is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN:
            Set depth to depth minus 1
        End If
        proc advance with parser
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DECLARATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level / member declaration dispatcher. Parses leading modifiers, then
branches on the declaration keyword. The modifier list is threaded into each
specific parser so data/sealed/etc. specialise the produced node type. An
unrecognised lead falls through to a statement/expression so member bodies stay
robust.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mods be proc parse_modifiers with parser
    Let t be proc cur with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_CLASS:
        Return proc parse_class with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE:
        Return proc parse_interface with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_OBJECT:
        Return proc parse_object with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FUN:
        Return proc parse_function with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_VAL:
        Return proc parse_property with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_VAR:
        Return proc parse_property with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TYPEALIAS:
        Return proc parse_typealias with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_ENUM:
        Return proc parse_enum with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_COMPANION:
        Return proc parse_companion with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CONSTRUCTOR:
        Return proc parse_secondary_constructor with parser, mods
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INIT:
        Return proc parse_init_block with parser
    End If

    Note: not a declaration keyword - treat as a statement
    Return proc parse_statement with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Decides whether a class is plain, data, sealed, annotation, or value based on
the collected modifiers, then parses an optional type-parameter list, an
optional primary constructor, an optional supertype list, an optional where
clause, and an optional class body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_class" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_CLASS
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser

    Let kind be KOTLIN_CLASS_DECLARATION
    If proc mods_contains with mods, "data" is equal to 1:
        Set kind to KOTLIN_DATA_CLASS
    End If
    If proc mods_contains with mods, "sealed" is equal to 1:
        Set kind to KOTLIN_SEALED_CLASS
    End If
    If proc mods_contains with mods, "annotation" is equal to 1:
        Set kind to KOTLIN_ANNOTATION_CLASS
    End If
    If proc mods_contains with mods, "enum" is equal to 1:
        Set kind to KOTLIN_ENUM_DECLARATION
    End If

    Let node be proc make_node with kind
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods

    Note: type parameters <T, out U : Bound>
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let tparams be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, tparams
    End If

    Note: primary constructor (val/var params)
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        Let ctor be proc parse_primary_constructor with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, ctor
    Otherwise:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_CONSTRUCTOR is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
                Let ctor2 be proc parse_primary_constructor with parser
                proc node_add_child with node, ctor2
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: supertypes : A(), B
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let supers be proc parse_supertype_list with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, supers
    End If

    Note: where clause
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_WHERE is equal to 1:
        Let wc be proc parse_where_clause with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, wc
    End If

    Note: class body
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_class_body with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If

    Return node
End Process

Process called "mods_contains" takes mods as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If mods is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with mods
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let m be proc get from List with mods, i
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with m, name is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_interface" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_INTERFACE
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INTERFACE_DECLARATION
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let tparams be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, tparams
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let supers be proc parse_supertype_list with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, supers
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_WHERE is equal to 1:
        Let wc be proc parse_where_clause with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, wc
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_class_body with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_object" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_OBJECT
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_OBJECT_DECLARATION
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let supers be proc parse_supertype_list with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, supers
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_class_body with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_companion" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_COMPANION
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_OBJECT
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_COMPANION_OBJECT
    Let name be 0
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER is equal to 1:
        Set name to proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
    End If
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let supers be proc parse_supertype_list with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, supers
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_class_body with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Enum class: `enum class Name { ENTRY1, ENTRY2(args); members }`. Parses the
entry list (comma separated, each an identifier with optional constructor
args), an optional trailing semicolon, then any member declarations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enum" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_ENUM
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_CLASS
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_ENUM_DECLARATION
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        Let ctor be proc parse_primary_constructor with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, ctor
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let supers be proc parse_supertype_list with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, supers
    End If

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Note: enum entries
        Let entries_looping be 1
        While entries_looping is equal to 1:
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER is equal to 1:
                Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
                Let entry be proc make_node with KOTLIN_ENUM_ENTRY
                Let ename be proc cur_text with parser
                proc advance with parser
                proc node_set_name with entry, ename
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
                    Let args be proc parse_argument_list with parser
                    proc node_add_child with entry, args
                End If
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
                    Let ebody be proc parse_class_body with parser
                    proc node_add_child with entry, ebody
                End If
                proc node_add_child with node, entry
                Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
                If after is equal to before:
                    proc force_advance with parser
                End If
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
                    proc advance with parser
                Otherwise:
                    Set entries_looping to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set entries_looping to 0
            End If
        End While
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON

        Note: remaining members
        While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 0:
            If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
                Set entries_looping to 0
                Return node
            End If
            Let mbefore be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            Let member be proc parse_declaration with parser
            proc node_add_child with node, member
            Let mafter be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            If mafter is equal to mbefore:
                proc force_advance with parser
            End If
        End While
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_typealias" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_TYPEALIAS
    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TYPEALIAS
    proc node_set_name with node, name
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let tparams be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, tparams
    End If
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN
    Let aliased be proc parse_type with parser
    proc node_set_type_ref with node, aliased
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A primary constructor parameter list `(val x: T = d, var y: U)`. Each parameter
may carry val/var (making it a property) and a default value. Parameters become
KOTLIN_PARAMETER children of a KOTLIN_PRIMARY_CONSTRUCTOR node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_primary_constructor" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PRIMARY_CONSTRUCTOR
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let param be proc parse_parameter with parser, 1
        proc node_add_child with node, param
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Note: no comma: must be the end
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
                If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 0:
                    Note: tolerate and continue toward RPAREN
                    Set before to before
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single parameter. allow_property=1 permits a leading val/var (primary-ctor
properties). Parses optional leading modifiers/annotations, the name, an
optional `: Type`, and an optional `= default`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_parameter" takes parser as Integer, allow_property as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PARAMETER

    Note: leading annotations/modifiers
    Let pmods be proc parse_modifiers with parser
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, pmods

    If allow_property is equal to 1:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_VAL is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            proc node_add_modifier with node, "val"
        Otherwise:
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_VAR is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
                proc node_add_modifier with node, "var"
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let name be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    proc node_set_name with node, name

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let ptype be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, ptype
    End If

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let default_val be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_set_aux1 with node, default_val
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Type parameter list `<out T : Bound, reified R>`. Each entry may carry a
variance modifier (out/in), the name, and an optional upper bound after ':'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_parameters" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LESS
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_WHERE_CLAUSE
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_GREATER is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let tp be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TYPE_PARAMETER

        Note: variance / reified modifiers
        Let vlooping be 1
        While vlooping is equal to 1:
            Let t be proc cur with parser
            If t is equal to TOKEN_OUT:
                proc node_add_modifier with tp, "out"
                proc advance with parser
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_IN:
                    proc node_add_modifier with tp, "in"
                    proc advance with parser
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_REIFIED:
                        proc node_add_modifier with tp, "reified"
                        proc advance with parser
                    Otherwise:
                        Set vlooping to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While

        Let tpname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with tp, tpname

        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let bound be proc parse_type with parser
            proc node_set_type_ref with tp, bound
        End If

        proc node_add_child with node, tp
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Set vlooping to 0
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_GREATER
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`where T : A, U : B` constraint clause. Each constraint is a type name, ':',
and a bound type.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_where_clause" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHERE
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_WHERE_CLAUSE
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let tp be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TYPE_PARAMETER
        Let tpname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with tp, tpname
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let bound be proc parse_type with parser
            proc node_set_type_ref with tp, bound
        End If
        proc node_add_child with node, tp
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Set looping to 0
        End If
    End While
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Supertype list after ':' in a class/interface/object header. Each supertype is
a type, optionally followed by a constructor-call argument list `()`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_supertype_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_SUPERTYPE
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let st be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, st
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
            proc skip_balanced_parens with parser
        End If
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_BY is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let deleg be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc node_add_child with node, deleg
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Set looping to 0
        End If
    End While
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Class body `{ member* }`. Parses members until the closing brace; force-advances
on zero progress so a malformed member cannot stall the loop.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_class_body" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Return node
        End If
        Let member be proc parse_declaration with parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc node_add_child with node, member
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FUNCTIONS AND PROPERTIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Function declaration: `fun <T> Receiver.name(params): RetType where ... { body }`
or expression body `= expr`. An optional receiver type before the name makes it
an extension function. Type params, params, return type, where clause, and body
are all optional and parsed in Kotlin's declared order.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_function" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_FUN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_FUNCTION_DECLARATION
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods

    Note: optional type parameters
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let tparams be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, tparams
    End If

    Note: name, possibly Receiver.name (extension)
    Let first be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_DOT is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Note: 'first' was the receiver type name; remaining is the function name
        proc node_set_value with node, first
        Set node to proc retag_extension with node
        Let fname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with node, fname
    Otherwise:
        proc node_set_name with node, first
    End If

    Note: parameters
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        Let params be proc parse_function_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, params
    End If

    Note: return type
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let rtype be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, rtype
    End If

    Note: where clause
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_WHERE is equal to 1:
        Let wc be proc parse_where_clause with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, wc
    End If

    Note: body - block or = expression
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    Otherwise:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let expr_body be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc node_set_aux1 with node, expr_body
            proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        End If
    End If

    Return node
End Process

Process called "retag_extension" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, KOTLIN_EXTENSION_FUNCTION
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Function parameter list `(name: T = d, ...)`. No val/var allowed here (those are
only on primary-constructor parameters), so parse_parameter is called with
allow_property=0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_function_parameters" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PRIMARY_CONSTRUCTOR
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let param be proc parse_parameter with parser, 0
        proc node_add_child with node, param
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Property declaration `val/var name: T = init` with optional getter/setter and an
optional `by delegate`. lateinit/const are carried as modifiers. The val/var
keyword sets a "var" or "val" value tag so the backend reproduces mutability.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_property" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_var be 0
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_VAR is equal to 1:
        Set is_var to 1
    End If
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PROPERTY_DECLARATION
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods
    If is_var is equal to 1:
        proc node_set_value with node, "var"
    Otherwise:
        proc node_set_value with node, "val"
    End If

    Note: optional type parameters (generic property/extension)
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let tparams be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, tparams
    End If

    Note: name, possibly Receiver.name extension property
    Let first be proc cur_text with parser
    proc advance with parser
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_DOT is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_aux2 with node, first
        Let pname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with node, pname
    Otherwise:
        proc node_set_name with node, first
    End If

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let ptype be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, ptype
    End If

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_BY is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let deleg be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_set_aux2 with node, deleg
    Otherwise:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let init_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc node_set_aux1 with node, init_expr
        End If
    End If

    Note: optional accessors get()/set()
    Let acc_looping be 1
    While acc_looping is equal to 1:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_GET is equal to 1:
            Let g be proc parse_accessor with parser, KOTLIN_GETTER
            proc node_add_child with node, g
        Otherwise:
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_SET is equal to 1:
                Let s be proc parse_accessor with parser, KOTLIN_SETTER
                proc node_add_child with node, s
            Otherwise:
                Set acc_looping to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_accessor" takes parser as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc make_node with kind
    proc advance with parser
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        proc skip_balanced_parens with parser
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let rtype be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, rtype
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    Otherwise:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let e be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc node_set_aux1 with node, e
        End If
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_secondary_constructor" takes parser as Integer, mods as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_CONSTRUCTOR
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_SECONDARY_CONSTRUCTOR
    proc copy_modifiers_to_node with node, mods
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        Let params be proc parse_function_parameters with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, params
    End If
    Note: delegation : this(...) / super(...)
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let deleg be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_set_aux1 with node, deleg
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_init_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_INIT
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INIT_BLOCK
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, body
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A type reference: a (possibly dotted) name, an optional generic argument list
`<A, B>`, and an optional trailing `?` for nullability. Function types
`(P) -> R` are handled by the leading-paren branch.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: function type or parenthesised type
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        Return proc parse_function_type with parser
    End If

    Let name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TYPE_REFERENCE
    proc node_set_name with node, name

    Note: generic arguments
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LESS is equal to 1:
        Let generic be proc make_node with KOTLIN_GENERIC_TYPE
        proc node_set_name with generic, name
        proc advance with parser
        While proc check with parser, TOKEN_GREATER is equal to 0:
            If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
                Return generic
            End If
            Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            Note: variance projection on type argument
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_OUT is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
            End If
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IN is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
            End If
            Note: star projection
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_STAR is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
                Let star be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TYPE_REFERENCE
                proc node_set_name with star, "*"
                proc node_add_child with generic, star
            Otherwise:
                Let arg be proc parse_type with parser
                proc node_add_child with generic, arg
            End If
            Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            If after is equal to before:
                proc force_advance with parser
            End If
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
            Otherwise:
                Set before to before
            End If
        End While
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_GREATER
        Set node to generic
    End If

    Note: nullable type
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let nullable be proc make_node with KOTLIN_NULLABLE_TYPE
        proc node_set_type_ref with nullable, node
        Set node to nullable
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Function type `(P1, P2) -> R`. The parameter types are collected as children of
a KOTLIN_FUNCTION_TYPE node whose type_ref holds the return type. A trailing
`?` makes a nullable function type.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_function_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_FUNCTION_TYPE
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let pt be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, pt
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ARROW is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let ret be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, ret
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let nullable be proc make_node with KOTLIN_NULLABLE_TYPE
        proc node_set_type_ref with nullable, node
        Return nullable
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STATEMENTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Block `{ stmt* }`. Each statement is parsed and force-advances on zero progress.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Return node
        End If
        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc node_add_child with node, stmt
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher. Local val/var declarations, control-flow keywords, and
otherwise an expression statement. Kotlin is expression-oriented, so if/when/try
parse as expressions when they appear in expression position; here at statement
position they are still parsed via the same routines and wrapped as statements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc cur with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_VAL:
        Return proc parse_local_property with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_VAR:
        Return proc parse_local_property with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_RETURN:
        Return proc parse_return with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_BREAK:
        proc advance with parser
        Let bnode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BREAK_STATEMENT
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ANNOTATION_USE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let lbl be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            proc node_set_value with bnode, lbl
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        Return bnode
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CONTINUE:
        proc advance with parser
        Let cnode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CONTINUE_STATEMENT
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ANNOTATION_USE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let lbl2 be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            proc node_set_value with cnode, lbl2
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        Return cnode
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_THROW:
        proc advance with parser
        Let thnode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_THROW_STATEMENT
        Let texpr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_add_child with thnode, texpr
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        Return thnode
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FOR:
        Return proc parse_for with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_WHILE:
        Return proc parse_while with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DO:
        Return proc parse_do_while with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FUN:
        Let lm be proc create from List
        Return proc parse_function with parser, lm
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CLASS:
        Let lm2 be proc create from List
        Return proc parse_class with parser, lm2
    End If

    Note: expression statement (covers if/when/try used as statements)
    Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Let stmt be proc make_node with KOTLIN_EXPRESSION_STATEMENT
    proc node_add_child with stmt, expr
    Return stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_local_property" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_var be 0
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_VAR is equal to 1:
        Set is_var to 1
    End If
    proc advance with parser
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_LOCAL_PROPERTY
    If is_var is equal to 1:
        proc node_set_value with node, "var"
    Otherwise:
        proc node_set_value with node, "val"
    End If

    Note: destructuring (a, b) = expr
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let names be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
        While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
            If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
                Return node
            End If
            Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            Let comp be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IDENTIFIER
            Let cname be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            proc node_set_name with comp, cname
            proc node_add_child with names, comp
            Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            If after is equal to before:
                proc force_advance with parser
            End If
            proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
        End While
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
        proc node_add_child with node, names
        proc node_set_name with node, "<destructuring>"
    Otherwise:
        Let name be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with node, name
    End If

    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let ptype be proc parse_type with parser
        proc node_set_type_ref with node, ptype
    End If
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let init_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_set_aux1 with node, init_expr
    End If
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_return" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RETURN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_RETURN_STATEMENT
    Note: labeled return return@label
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ANNOTATION_USE is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let lbl be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_value with node, lbl
    End If
    Note: optional return value (none if at block end / brace / semicolon)
    Let t be proc cur with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE:
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        Return node
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON:
        proc advance with parser
        Return node
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_EOF:
        Return node
    End If
    Let val_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, val_expr
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`for (x in collection) body`. The loop variable (or destructuring), the `in`
iterable expression, and the body are children/fields.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_for" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_FOR
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_FOR_STATEMENT
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Note: loop variable
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        proc skip_balanced_parens with parser
        proc node_set_name with node, "<destructuring>"
    Otherwise:
        Let vname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with node, vname
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let vtype be proc parse_type with parser
            proc node_set_type_ref with node, vtype
        End If
    End If
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IN
    Let iter be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc node_set_aux1 with node, iter
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Let body be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, body
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_while" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHILE
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_WHILE_STATEMENT
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc node_set_aux1 with node, cond
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Let body be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, body
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_do_while" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_DO
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_DO_WHILE_STATEMENT
    Let body be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, body
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHILE
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc node_set_aux1 with node, cond
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_statement_or_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
        Return proc parse_block with parser
    End If
    Return proc parse_statement with parser
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EXPRESSIONS (precedence climbing)
Note: Kotlin precedence (low->high): assignment, disjunction (||), conjunction
Note: (&&), equality (== != === !==), comparison (< > <= >=), named-infix &
Note: elvis (?:), range (..), additive (+ -), multiplicative (* / %), prefix,
Note: postfix (call, member, index, !!), primary.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc parse_assignment with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Assignment / compound assignment is right-associative and lowest precedence. We
parse a disjunction, and if an assignment operator follows, recurse on the RHS.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_assignment" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_elvis with parser
    Let t be proc cur with parser
    If proc is_assign_op with t is equal to 1:
        Let op be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let right be proc parse_assignment with parser
        Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_ASSIGNMENT
        proc node_set_value with node, op
        proc node_add_child with node, left
        proc node_add_child with node, right
        Return node
    End If
    Return left
End Process

Process called "is_assign_op" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PLUS_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_MINUS_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_STAR_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SLASH_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT_ASSIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_elvis" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_disjunction with parser
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_ELVIS is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let right be proc parse_disjunction with parser
        Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_ELVIS_EXPRESSION
        proc node_add_child with node, left
        proc node_add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_disjunction" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_conjunction with parser
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_OR is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let right be proc parse_conjunction with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with "||", left, right
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_conjunction" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_equality with parser
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_AND is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let right be proc parse_equality with parser
        Set left to proc make_binary with "&&", left, right
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_equality" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_comparison with parser
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL:
            proc advance with parser
            Let r1 be proc parse_comparison with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with "==", left, r1
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL:
                proc advance with parser
                Let r2 be proc parse_comparison with parser
                Set left to proc make_binary with "!=", left, r2
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL_REF:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let r3 be proc parse_comparison with parser
                    Set left to proc make_binary with "===", left, r3
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL_REF:
                        proc advance with parser
                        Let r4 be proc parse_comparison with parser
                        Set left to proc make_binary with "!==", left, r4
                    Otherwise:
                        Set looping to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_comparison" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_named_infix with parser
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_LESS:
            proc advance with parser
            Let r1 be proc parse_named_infix with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with "<", left, r1
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER:
                proc advance with parser
                Let r2 be proc parse_named_infix with parser
                Set left to proc make_binary with ">", left, r2
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_LESS_EQUAL:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let r3 be proc parse_named_infix with parser
                    Set left to proc make_binary with "<=", left, r3
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_GREATER_EQUAL:
                        proc advance with parser
                        Let r4 be proc parse_named_infix with parser
                        Set left to proc make_binary with ">=", left, r4
                    Otherwise:
                        Set looping to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Named-infix level handles `is`/`!is`/`in`/`!in` type and membership checks plus
user infix functions (identifier used as an infix operator). This sits between
comparison and range per the Kotlin grammar.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_named_infix" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_range with parser
    Note: At a when-arm body boundary, a leading is/!is/in/infix-identifier
    Note: actually begins the NEXT arm (the real separator is a newline the lexer
    Note: dropped). Suppress the continuation so the body stays a single expr.
    If proc get_in_when_body with parser is equal to 1:
        proc set_in_when_body with parser, 0
        Return left
    End If
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_IS:
            proc advance with parser
            Let ty be proc parse_type with parser
            Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IS_EXPRESSION
            proc node_set_value with node, "is"
            proc node_add_child with node, left
            proc node_set_type_ref with node, ty
            Set left to node
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT:
                Note: !is / !in
                Let nt be proc peek_is_not_infix with parser
                If nt is equal to 1:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Note: now at IS or IN
                    Let t2 be proc cur with parser
                    proc advance with parser
                    If t2 is equal to TOKEN_IS:
                        Let ty2 be proc parse_type with parser
                        Let node2 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IS_EXPRESSION
                        proc node_set_value with node2, "!is"
                        proc node_add_child with node2, left
                        proc node_set_type_ref with node2, ty2
                        Set left to node2
                    Otherwise:
                        Let r be proc parse_range with parser
                        Set left to proc make_binary with "!in", left, r
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set looping to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_IN:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let rin be proc parse_range with parser
                    Set left to proc make_binary with "in", left, rin
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
                        Note: user infix function: identifier between operands.
                        Let opname be proc cur_text with parser
                        proc advance with parser
                        Let rinf be proc parse_range with parser
                        Let inode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INFIX_EXPRESSION
                        proc node_set_value with inode, opname
                        proc node_add_child with inode, left
                        proc node_add_child with inode, rinf
                        Set left to inode
                    Otherwise:
                        Set looping to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "peek_is_not_infix" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: We are at '!'. Peek the lexer one token ahead without committing using a
    Note: cheap heuristic: tokenise the next token from a cloned cursor. Because
    Note: cloning the lexer is non-trivial here, we conservatively only treat '!'
    Note: as a !is/!in lead when the immediate next source token is 'is' or 'in'.
    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Note: skip spaces
    Let p be pos
    While p is less than len:
        Let c be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, p
        If c is equal to 32:
            Set p to p plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If c is equal to 9:
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set p to len plus len
            End If
        End If
        If p is greater than len:
            Set p to p minus len
            Set p to p minus len
            Set p to p
        End If
    End While
    Note: simplest robust check: compare next two bytes
    Let b0 be 0
    Let b1 be 0
    If pos is less than len:
        Set b0 to proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, pos
    End If
    If pos plus 1 is less than len:
        Set b1 to proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, pos plus 1
    End If
    Note: 'is' = 105,115 ; 'in' = 105,110
    If b0 is equal to 105:
        If b1 is equal to 115:
            Return 1
        End If
        If b1 is equal to 110:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_range" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_additive with parser
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RANGE is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let right be proc parse_additive with parser
        Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_RANGE_EXPRESSION
        proc node_set_value with node, ".."
        proc node_add_child with node, left
        proc node_add_child with node, right
        Set left to node
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_additive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_multiplicative with parser
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_PLUS:
            proc advance with parser
            Let r1 be proc parse_multiplicative with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with "+", left, r1
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_MINUS:
                proc advance with parser
                Let r2 be proc parse_multiplicative with parser
                Set left to proc make_binary with "-", left, r2
            Otherwise:
                Set looping to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_multiplicative" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc parse_prefix with parser
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_STAR:
            proc advance with parser
            Let r1 be proc parse_prefix with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary with "*", left, r1
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_SLASH:
                proc advance with parser
                Let r2 be proc parse_prefix with parser
                Set left to proc make_binary with "/", left, r2
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let r3 be proc parse_prefix with parser
                    Set left to proc make_binary with "%", left, r3
                Otherwise:
                    Set looping to 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Prefix operators: unary +/-, logical not (!), pre-increment/decrement. Each
wraps the parsed operand in a unary expression carrying the operator text.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_prefix" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc cur with parser
    If t is equal to TOKEN_MINUS:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand be proc parse_prefix with parser
        Return proc make_unary with "-", operand
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_PLUS:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand2 be proc parse_prefix with parser
        Return proc make_unary with "+", operand2
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand3 be proc parse_prefix with parser
        Return proc make_unary with "!", operand3
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INCREMENT:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand4 be proc parse_prefix with parser
        Return proc make_unary with "++", operand4
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DECREMENT:
        proc advance with parser
        Let operand5 be proc parse_prefix with parser
        Return proc make_unary with "--", operand5
    End If
    Return proc parse_postfix with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Postfix: call `(args)`, trailing-lambda call `f { ... }`, member access `.x`,
safe access `?.x`, index `[i]`, not-null `!!`, callable reference `::x`, and
post inc/dec. Each loop iteration force-advances on zero progress.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_postfix" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let expr be proc parse_primary with parser
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let t be proc cur with parser

        If t is equal to TOKEN_DOT:
            proc advance with parser
            Let mname be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_MEMBER_ACCESS
            proc node_set_name with node, mname
            proc node_add_child with node, expr
            Set expr to node
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_SAFE_CALL:
                proc advance with parser
                Let sname be proc cur_text with parser
                proc advance with parser
                Let snode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_SAFE_ACCESS
                proc node_set_name with snode, sname
                proc node_add_child with snode, expr
                Set expr to snode
            Otherwise:
                If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN:
                    Let args be proc parse_argument_list with parser
                    Let cnode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CALL_EXPRESSION
                    proc node_add_child with cnode, expr
                    proc node_add_child with cnode, args
                    Note: trailing lambda
                    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 1:
                        Let tl be proc parse_lambda with parser
                        proc node_add_child with cnode, tl
                    End If
                    Set expr to cnode
                Otherwise:
                    If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE:
                        Note: trailing lambda with no parens: f { ... }
                        Let tl2 be proc parse_lambda with parser
                        Let cnode2 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CALL_EXPRESSION
                        proc node_add_child with cnode2, expr
                        Let empty_args be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
                        proc node_add_child with cnode2, empty_args
                        proc node_add_child with cnode2, tl2
                        Set expr to cnode2
                    Otherwise:
                        If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET:
                            Let idx be proc parse_index with parser
                            proc node_add_child with idx, expr
                            Set expr to idx
                        Otherwise:
                            If t is equal to TOKEN_NOT_NULL:
                                proc advance with parser
                                Let nn be proc make_node with KOTLIN_NOT_NULL_EXPRESSION
                                proc node_add_child with nn, expr
                                Set expr to nn
                            Otherwise:
                                If t is equal to TOKEN_DOUBLE_COLON:
                                    proc advance with parser
                                    Let rname be proc cur_text with parser
                                    proc advance with parser
                                    Let cr be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CALLABLE_REFERENCE
                                    proc node_set_name with cr, rname
                                    proc node_add_child with cr, expr
                                    Set expr to cr
                                Otherwise:
                                    If t is equal to TOKEN_INCREMENT:
                                        proc advance with parser
                                        Let pi be proc make_node with KOTLIN_POSTFIX_EXPRESSION
                                        proc node_set_value with pi, "++"
                                        proc node_add_child with pi, expr
                                        Set expr to pi
                                    Otherwise:
                                        If t is equal to TOKEN_DECREMENT:
                                            proc advance with parser
                                            Let pd be proc make_node with KOTLIN_POSTFIX_EXPRESSION
                                            proc node_set_value with pd, "--"
                                            proc node_add_child with pd, expr
                                            Set expr to pd
                                        Otherwise:
                                            If t is equal to TOKEN_AS:
                                                proc advance with parser
                                                Let safe_as be 0
                                                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION is equal to 1:
                                                    proc advance with parser
                                                    Set safe_as to 1
                                                End If
                                                Let asty be proc parse_type with parser
                                                Let asn be proc make_node with KOTLIN_AS_EXPRESSION
                                                If safe_as is equal to 1:
                                                    proc node_set_value with asn, "as?"
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    proc node_set_value with asn, "as"
                                                End If
                                                proc node_add_child with asn, expr
                                                proc node_set_type_ref with asn, asty
                                                Set expr to asn
                                            Otherwise:
                                                Set looping to 0
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            If looping is equal to 1:
                Set looping to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return expr
End Process

Process called "parse_index" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INDEX_ACCESS
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let idx_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, idx_expr
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Argument list `(a, name = b, *spread)`. Each argument may be named (`name =`)
or a spread (`*expr`); both are recorded on a KOTLIN_ARGUMENT wrapper.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_argument_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let arg be proc make_node with KOTLIN_ARGUMENT

        Note: named argument: IDENT '=' expr
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER is equal to 1:
            Let saved be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            Let aname be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
                proc node_set_name with arg, aname
                Let ae be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc node_add_child with arg, ae
            Otherwise:
                Note: not a named arg; rebuild as identifier-led expression.
                Let id be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IDENTIFIER
                proc node_set_name with id, aname
                Let full be proc continue_postfix with parser, id
                proc node_add_child with arg, full
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_STAR is equal to 1:
                proc advance with parser
                proc node_set_value with arg, "*"
                Let se be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc node_add_child with arg, se
            Otherwise:
                Let e be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc node_add_child with arg, e
            End If
        End If

        proc node_add_child with node, arg
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
After an identifier has been consumed (e.g. when a named-argument lookahead
failed), continue the postfix chain on that identifier so the full expression
(calls, member access, etc.) is captured. Mirrors parse_postfix but seeded with
an already-built primary.
@End Reasoning
Process called "continue_postfix" takes parser as Integer, seed as Integer returns Integer:
    Let expr be seed
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let t be proc cur with parser
        If t is equal to TOKEN_DOT:
            proc advance with parser
            Let mname be proc cur_text with parser
            proc advance with parser
            Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_MEMBER_ACCESS
            proc node_set_name with node, mname
            proc node_add_child with node, expr
            Set expr to node
        Otherwise:
            If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN:
                Let args be proc parse_argument_list with parser
                Let cnode be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CALL_EXPRESSION
                proc node_add_child with cnode, expr
                proc node_add_child with cnode, args
                Set expr to cnode
            Otherwise:
                Set looping to 0
            End If
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            Set looping to 0
        End If
    End While
    Note: allow remaining binary operators after the seeded identifier
    Return expr
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PRIMARY EXPRESSIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Primary expression: literals, identifiers, this/super, parenthesised group,
lambda block, if/when expression, try expression, and string templates. Every
branch consumes at least one token (or, for the paren/brace forms, a balanced
region), so parse_primary always advances - the postfix and binary loops above
rely on this to remain progress-guaranteed.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_primary" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc cur with parser

    If t is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER_LITERAL:
        Let v be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INTEGER_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n, v
        Return n
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_LONG_LITERAL:
        Let v2 be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n2 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_INTEGER_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n2, v2
        Return n2
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT_LITERAL:
        Let v3 be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n3 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_FLOAT_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n3, v3
        Return n3
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL:
        Let v4 be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n4 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_STRING_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n4, v4
        Return n4
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_MULTILINE_STRING:
        Let v5 be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n5 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_STRING_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n5, v5
        proc node_set_aux2 with n5, "multiline"
        Return n5
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_CHAR_LITERAL:
        Let v6 be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let n6 be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CHAR_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with n6, v6
        Return n6
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TRUE:
        proc advance with parser
        Let nt be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BOOL_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with nt, "true"
        Return nt
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_FALSE:
        proc advance with parser
        Let nf be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BOOL_LITERAL
        proc node_set_value with nf, "false"
        Return nf
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_NULL:
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc make_node with KOTLIN_NULL_LITERAL
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_THIS:
        proc advance with parser
        Let th be proc make_node with KOTLIN_THIS_EXPRESSION
        proc node_set_value with th, "this"
        Return th
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SUPER:
        proc advance with parser
        Let su be proc make_node with KOTLIN_SUPER_EXPRESSION
        proc node_set_value with su, "super"
        Return su
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_IF:
        Return proc parse_if_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_WHEN:
        Return proc parse_when_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_TRY:
        Return proc parse_try_expression with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN:
        proc advance with parser
        Let inner be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
        Return inner
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE:
        Return proc parse_lambda with parser
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let id be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IDENTIFIER
        proc node_set_name with id, name
        Return id
    End If

    Note: Soft keywords used as identifiers in expression position
    If proc is_soft_keyword with t is equal to 1:
        Let skname be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let skid be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IDENTIFIER
        proc node_set_name with skid, skname
        Return skid
    End If

    Note: Unknown lead - consume one token to guarantee progress and emit an
    Note: identifier carrying the raw lexeme so the tree stays well-formed.
    Let raw be proc cur_text with parser
    If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 0:
        proc advance with parser
    End If
    Let fallback be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IDENTIFIER
    proc node_set_name with fallback, raw
    Return fallback
End Process

Process called "is_soft_keyword" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to TOKEN_GET:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_SET:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_DATA:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_OUT:
        Return 1
    End If
    If t is equal to TOKEN_INNER:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
`if (cond) then else else_branch` as an expression. Branches may be blocks or
expressions; both are parsed via parse_statement_or_block to capture either form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_if_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IF
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IF_EXPRESSION
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
    Let cond be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc node_set_aux1 with node, cond
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    Let then_branch be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, then_branch
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ELSE is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let else_branch be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with node, else_branch
    End If
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`when (subject?) { pattern -> body ; else -> body }`. Subject is optional. Each
entry has one or more comma-separated conditions (or `else`), an arrow, and a
body. A guard form `cond -> ...` is captured as the condition expression.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_when_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHEN
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_WHEN_EXPRESSION
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let subject be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc node_set_aux1 with node, subject
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
    End If
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        Let entry be proc make_node with KOTLIN_WHEN_ENTRY

        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ELSE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            proc node_set_value with entry, "else"
        Otherwise:
            Note: comma-separated conditions until ->
            Let cond_looping be 1
            While cond_looping is equal to 1:
                Let cbefore be proc lexer_cursor with parser
                Note: is / in conditions
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IS is equal to 1:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let cty be proc parse_type with parser
                    Let isc be proc make_node with KOTLIN_IS_EXPRESSION
                    proc node_set_value with isc, "is"
                    proc node_set_type_ref with isc, cty
                    proc node_add_child with entry, isc
                Otherwise:
                    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_IN is equal to 1:
                        proc advance with parser
                        Let inr be proc parse_expression with parser
                        Let inc be proc make_node with KOTLIN_RANGE_EXPRESSION
                        proc node_set_value with inc, "in"
                        proc node_add_child with inc, inr
                        proc node_add_child with entry, inc
                    Otherwise:
                        Let ce be proc parse_expression with parser
                        proc node_add_child with entry, ce
                    End If
                End If
                Let cafter be proc lexer_cursor with parser
                If cafter is equal to cbefore:
                    proc force_advance with parser
                End If
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COMMA is equal to 1:
                    proc advance with parser
                Otherwise:
                    Set cond_looping to 0
                End If
            End While
        End If

        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_ARROW
        Note: For a non-block arm body, suppress is/in/infix continuation so the
        Note: next arm's leading is/in is not absorbed into this body expression.
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE is equal to 0:
            proc set_in_when_body with parser, 1
        End If
        Let body be proc parse_statement_or_block with parser
        proc set_in_when_body with parser, 0
        proc node_add_child with entry, body
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        proc node_add_child with node, entry

        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
`try { } catch (e: T) { } finally { }`. The try block is the first child;
catch clauses follow as KOTLIN_CATCH_CLAUSE children; an optional finally block
is stored in aux1.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_try_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_TRY
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_TRY_STATEMENT
    Let try_block be proc parse_block with parser
    proc node_add_child with node, try_block
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_CATCH is equal to 1:
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        proc advance with parser
        Let catch_node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_CATCH_CLAUSE
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN
        Let ename be proc cur_text with parser
        proc advance with parser
        proc node_set_name with catch_node, ename
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Let ety be proc parse_type with parser
            proc node_set_type_ref with catch_node, ety
        End If
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN
        Let cbody be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_add_child with catch_node, cbody
        proc node_add_child with node, catch_node
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    If proc check with parser, TOKEN_FINALLY is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Let fblock be proc parse_block with parser
        proc node_set_aux1 with node, fblock
    End If
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lambda `{ params -> body }` or `{ body }` (implicit `it`). The optional parameter
list precedes the arrow. The body is a sequence of statements. Lambda params are
stored as a KOTLIN_BLOCK child first (when present), then the body statements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_lambda" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION

    Note: detect a parameter list followed by '->'. We scan parameters; if no
    Note: arrow appears the scanned identifiers are actually body statements, but
    Note: to keep the parser single-pass and progress-guaranteed we only treat a
    Note: leading IDENT/comma-IDENT run terminated by ARROW as parameters.
    Let params be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BLOCK
    Let has_params be proc try_parse_lambda_params with parser, params
    If has_params is equal to 1:
        proc node_add_child with node, params
        proc node_set_value with node, "params"
    End If

    Note: body statements
    While proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 0:
        If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
            Return node
        End If
        Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        proc accept with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Return node
        End If
        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc node_add_child with node, stmt
        End If
        Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
        If after is equal to before:
            proc force_advance with parser
        End If
    End While
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Heuristic single-pass lambda parameter detection: parameters are a run of
identifiers (optionally `name: Type`) separated by commas and terminated by
`->`. Because we cannot cheaply backtrack the lexer, we scan source bytes ahead
for the first of `->` or `}`/`;` at the top brace level to decide whether a
parameter list is present before committing. Returns 1 and fills params when an
arrow-terminated parameter list exists, else 0 (cursor unchanged).
@End Reasoning
Process called "try_parse_lambda_params" takes parser as Integer, params as Integer returns Integer:
    Let has_arrow be proc lambda_has_arrow_ahead with parser
    If has_arrow is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let looping be 1
    While looping is equal to 1:
        If proc check with parser, TOKEN_ARROW is equal to 1:
            proc advance with parser
            Set looping to 0
        Otherwise:
            If proc at_eof with parser is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let before be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            Note: destructured param (a, b)
            If proc check with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN is equal to 1:
                proc skip_balanced_parens with parser
            Otherwise:
                Let pname be proc cur_text with parser
                proc advance with parser
                Let p be proc make_node with KOTLIN_PARAMETER
                proc node_set_name with p, pname
                If proc check with parser, TOKEN_COLON is equal to 1:
                    proc advance with parser
                    Let pty be proc parse_type with parser
                    proc node_set_type_ref with p, pty
                End If
                proc node_add_child with params, p
            End If
            proc accept with parser, TOKEN_COMMA
            Let after be proc lexer_cursor with parser
            If after is equal to before:
                proc force_advance with parser
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Looks ahead in the raw source from the current lexer cursor to determine whether
a top-level `->` appears before the matching `}` or a `{`/`(` that would open a
nested scope. This is a bounded forward byte scan (no allocation, no token
production) used solely to disambiguate `{ params -> body }` from `{ body }`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lambda_has_arrow_ahead" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let depth be 0
    Let p be pos
    Let result be 0
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If p is greater than or equal to len:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let c be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, p
            If c is equal to 123:
                Set depth to depth plus 1
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If c is equal to 125:
                    If depth is equal to 0:
                        Set scanning to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Set depth to depth minus 1
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    If c is equal to 59:
                        If depth is equal to 0:
                            Set scanning to 0
                        Otherwise:
                            Set p to p plus 1
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If c is equal to 45:
                            Let c2 be 0
                            If p plus 1 is less than len:
                                Set c2 to proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, p plus 1
                            End If
                            If c2 is equal to 62:
                                If depth is equal to 0:
                                    Set result to 1
                                    Set scanning to 0
                                Otherwise:
                                    Set p to p plus 1
                                End If
                            Otherwise:
                                Set p to p plus 1
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Set p to p plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BINARY / UNARY HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "make_binary" takes op as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_BINARY_EXPRESSION
    proc node_set_value with node, op
    proc node_add_child with node, left
    proc node_add_child with node, right
    Return node
End Process

Process called "make_unary" takes op as Integer, operand as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc make_node with KOTLIN_UNARY_EXPRESSION
    proc node_set_value with node, op
    proc node_add_child with node, operand
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
